STATE/COUNTY FIPS CODE NUMBERS WITH ASSIGNED MSA NUMBER - OWCP - U.S. Department of Labor
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF LABOR, OWCP FEE SCHEDULE
STATE/COUNTY FIPS CODE NUMBERS WITH ASSIGNED MSA NUMBER
Note:  This file is used with the MSA file Effective_May_16_2004_MSA
ASSIGNMENT OF GEOGRAPHIC ADJUSTMENTS BY STATE & COUNTY
This file is used to locate Geographic Practice Cost Index values (GPCI) for a county/ territory/borough within
a state.  Each state's areas are listed in alphabetical order.
This file is also used to match U.S. Postal Service ZIP code tables which designate MSA or RURAL AREAs by
state and county FIPS codes to the OWCP GAF areas.  The FIPS codes are uniform on both tables.  The 
Geographic Practice Cost Index (GPCI) for each county/borough area are found by MSA number on file fs03gpci.  
A file that links provider's ZIP code to the OWCP GPCI values may be created using three files:
a USPS ZIP code file with FIPS codes, fs04ctst, and fs04gpci.
The state code is the first 2 characters under ST/CTY and the county code is the last three characters 
under ST/CTY.  Where the MSA/PMSA/NECMA column shows a "0", the county belongs to the state rural area and 
those RVU values apply.  Where there is a MSA/PMSA/NECMA number listed for the county, use the GPCI 
values for that MSA.  Each MSA has a GPCI value for work, practice expense, and malpractice.
Example:  FIPS code=01003.  The state code=01, county code=003.  This represents Baldwin County, AL
The MSA number is 5160.  Use GPCI values listed under MSA 5160 in the file:  fs04gpci.
